I will not be going back. I ordered the California omelet. Got it and was surprised to see onions all in it. Onions are not supposed to be in the omelet, and I HATE them. We couldn't get the waitress. She rarely checked on us and we had to call for help numerous times before just to get someone to finally refill our drink. Food finally came and this happened. Finally, I was able to flag her down. She didn't even apologize when she took it back. It took a while to get the new one. Asked to speak to the manager and she claimed there was no manager there. When asked if she would comp something for the trouble, she said no. By the time my food finally came out my friend had already finished eating. Finally a manager, who apparently wasn't there according to the waitress, came to apologize. Nothing was comped and the waitress never once apologized. The omelet was actually mediocre, too. I will not be back. Poor service and poor food.  We were really excited to check out a neighborhood favorite while we were in town, but this was just horrible. We asked to sit outside and then the server brought us water and did not return for 5 minutes as we sat without menus. She came back and apologized then got us a menu and did Not return for 10 minutes. After that, we decided to sit at the bar so we could at least order. She complained to another server that she was too busy to get to us and then took our order after a few minutes. I ordered the eggs portchartrain and my husband ordered the crab cake benedict. The crawfish was so salty that it was inedible, there was way too much hollondaise sauce over the plate, and the eggs were poached for too long. She never asked how our food was despite standing five feet away from us. Poor service and poor food, I won’t be returning.
